				<text>37.2.1.1 Using the binomial model</text>
		</name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise</p><p>Using the binomial model, and assuming that a success occurs with probability \(\dfrac{1}{{@den_prob@}}\) in each trial, find the probability that in {@num_trials@} trials there are&nbsp;<br></p>
<ol class="HELM_parts_inline">
<li>0 successes</li>
<li>{@num_succ@} successes</li>
<li>{@num_fail@} failures.</li>
</ol>
<p>Let \(X\) be the number of successes in {@num_trials@} independent trials. <b>Note:</b> Please round your answer to the nearest 2 decimal places.</p>
<ol class="HELM_parts">

<li><p>\(\text{P} (X=0)=\) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]</p></li>

<li><p>\(\text{P} (X={@num_succ@})=\) [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]] [[feedback:prt2]]</p></li>

<li><p>\(\text{P} (X={@num_trials - num_fail@})=\) [[input:ans3]] [[validation:ans3]] [[feedback:prt3]]</p></li>

</ol>]]></text>
		</questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<b>SOLUTION:</b><p><br></p><p>In each case \( p=\dfrac{1}{{@den_prob@}} \) and \( q=1-p=\dfrac{{@den_prob - 1@}}{{@den_prob@}}\).</p><p><br></p>
<ol class="HELM_parts">

<li><p>Here \(r=0\) and</p><p>\(\text{P}(X=0) = q^{@num_trials@} = \left( \dfrac{{@den_prob - 1@}}{{@den_prob@}} \right)^{@num_trials@} = \dfrac{{@(den_prob - 1)^num_trials@}}{{@den_prob^num_trials@}} \approx {@ta_1@}  \)</p></li>

<li><p>Here \(r={@num_succ@}\) and \(\text{P} (X={@num_succ@})= ^{@num_trials@}C_{@num_succ@}p^{@num_succ@}q^{@num_trials - num_succ@} = \dfrac{{@num_trials@}!}{{@num_succ@}!({@num_trials@}-{@num_succ@})!} \times \left(&nbsp;\dfrac{1}{{@den_prob@}} \right)^{@num_succ@} \times&nbsp;\left(&nbsp;\dfrac{{@den_prob - 1@}}{{@den_prob@}}&nbsp;\right)^{@num_trials - num_succ@} \approx {@ta_2@}&nbsp;\)&nbsp;</p></li>

<li><p>Here \(r={@num_trials - num_fail@}\) and \(\text{P} (X={@num_trials - num_fail@})= ^{@num_trials@}C_{@num_trials - num_fail@}p^{@num_trials - num_fail@}q^{@num_fail@} = \dfrac{{@num_trials@}!}{{@num_trials - num_fail@}!({@num_trials@}-{@num_trials - num_fail@})!} \times \left(&nbsp;\dfrac{1}{{@den_prob@}}&nbsp;\right)^{@num_trials - num_fail@} \times&nbsp;\left(&nbsp;\dfrac{{@den_prob - 1@}}{{@den_prob@}}&nbsp;\right)^{@num_fail@} \approx {@ta_3@}&nbsp;\)</p></li>

</ol>]]></text>
		</generalfeedback>
